      <div xml:id="Aink250-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">
          <p>talaimakaṭku vanta nōy murukaṉāl vantamai ikkaḻaṅku kūṟiṟṟu eṉṟu vēlaṉ coṉṉāṉ eṉpatu
      kēṭṭa tōḻi akkaḻaṅkiṟku uraippāḷāyc cevili kēṭkumāṟṟāl aṟattoṭu nilai kuṟittuc colliyatu</p>
        </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>What the friend, standing [in accordance] with duty, said as one who spoke to the Molucca-bean by the way of foster-mother listening; [the friend who]
      listened to the Vēlaṉ who said that this Molucca-bean declared the pain that had
      befallen the heroine to have come about by Murukaṉ. <div xml:id="Aink250">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l>poypaṭu paṟiyāk kaḻaṅkē meyyē</l>
          <l>maṇivaraik kaṭci maṭamayi lālu nam</l>
          <l>malarnta vaḷḷiyaṅ kāṉaṅ kiḻavō</l>
          <l>ṉāṇṭakai viṟalvē ḷallaṉivaḷ</l>
          <l>pūṇṭāṅ kiḷamulai yaṇaṅki yōṉē</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Oh Molucca-bean unaware of the occurrence of falsehood,</l>
          <l>the truth, in fact, </l>
          <l>is that he who tormented her ornament-bearing young breasts, </l>
          <l> – our master of the woodland with bloomed creepers,</l>
          <l>where naïve peacocks dance in the forests of sapphire mountains, </l>
          <l>is not the victorious Vēḷ worthy of manhood. </l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
